{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"77b83bb3-3076-4804-a49e-786a33e1fc2d","content":"To switch from VSTest to Microsoft.Testing.Platform with MSTest.Sdk/3.8.0, you need to make these changes in your project file:\n\n1. **Remove** (or set to `false`) the VSTest property:\n   ```xml\n   <!-- Delete this line -->\n   <UseVSTest>true</UseVSTest>\n   ```\n\n2. That's it. MSTest.Sdk 3.8.0 uses Microsoft.Testing.Platform **by default** when `UseVSTest` is not set (or is `false`).\n\n**Key differences to be aware of:**\n\n- **Run tests** with `dotnet test` as before (it works with both runners), or use `dotnet run` directly on the test project (the new platform makes test projects executable).\n- **CLI options change** — e.g., `--filter` becomes `--filter` still works but some VSTest-specific options differ. Use `dotnet test -- --help` to see new options.\n- **`.runsettings`** are still supported, but some platform-specific settings may need adjustment.\n- **Extensions** — if you use VSTest adapters/extensions, verify they have Microsoft.Testing.Platform equivalents.","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"2601b121-5b23-4838-ae00-a01580d64f22","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"The user is asking about migrating from VSTest to Microsoft.Testing.Platform in an MSTest project that uses MSTest.Sdk/3.8.0. This is a knowledge question about .NET testing configuration. Let me provide a concise answer based on my knowledge.","outputTokens":353,"requestId":"4C1B:7C3A8:D7C72A:10BDC2C:6A0129B7"},"id":"3ec07ed2-a39b-45e3-9df9-ba146c5cc243","timestamp":"2026-05-11T00:58:40.459Z","parentId":"6327310b-c6e9-4ce4-b116-274b472ac8e0"}
